title: New York City Department of City Planning, City Counsel District Boundaries, New York City, 2008
name: New York City Department of City Planning, City Counsel District Boundaries, New York City, 2008
description:
The City Council Districts are the result of the recent redistricting process, which takes place every ten years to reflect population changes reported in the 2000 Census. These geographies were redrawn by the New York City Council Redistricting Commission.
These districts were created by the Department of City Planning to aid city agencies in administering public services.

author.source: New York City Department of City Planning
